OL,5,Cplans
OL,7,F"It is entirely normal for staff to
OL,8,Fhave discussions with potential
OL,9,Fpartners to assess feasibility before
OL,10,Fbringing proposals to cabinet and the
OL,11,Fcouncil's other committees. This is
OL,12,Fnecessary to allow us to carry out due
OL,13,Fdiligence and risk assessments in the
OL,14,Fpublic interest. The emails show
OL,15,Fpoints for discussion at a preliminary
OL,16,Fmeeting suggested by the potential
OL,17,Foperator. These were their suggested
OL,18,Fterms not ours and do not reflect the
OL,19,Ffinal agreement.
